import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of life expectancy over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['country', 'fertility']]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 10))
    ax.boxplot(data.groupby('country')['fertility'].apply(list).values)
    ax.set_xticklabels(data.groupby('country')['fertility'].apply(list).index, rotation=90)
    ax.set_xlabel('Country')
    ax.set_ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility rate across different countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['pop', 'life_expect'])
    plt.scatter(data['pop'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.title('What is the relationship between population and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['cluster'] = data['cluster'].astype(str)
    data = data.groupby('cluster').mean()[['life_expect', 'fertility']]
    ax = data.plot(kind='bar', rot=0, figsize=(10,6))
    ax.set_xlabel('Cluster')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average')
    ax.axhline(data['life_expect'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Avg Life Expectancy')
    ax.axhline(data['fertility'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Avg Fertility Rate')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average life expectancy and fertility rate for each cluster?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['pop'] = data['pop'].astype(float)
    data = data.groupby(['cluster'])['pop'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['cluster'], data['pop'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different clusters?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Cluster')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
